Hence we find that whilst in certain cases there is an almost servile repetition of whole chapters, in other parts not only words are altered but whole passages of considerable length are inserted and others are taken out. Some chapters are placed in a different order, and in other cases left out. Moreover, in addition to these differences, this work contains a new account of the Canonization and a most elaborate version of the Miracles, which latter constitutes nearly half of the volume, and is, be it noted, not an addition to, but an essential part of the work.
